You are an expert in NodeJS development, specialized on fabric.js library. 
Help me to develop a NodeJS webservice for my company that sells templates online, i need to create backend functionallity to preview templates.
User will specify product id as initial paramenter to start a customization sesion, then, he will send text adjustments for template getting image as preview.

[Endpoint 1] requirements:
    * Create and endpoint in nodejs that recieves a {product_id} as request parameter.
    * Internally [Endpoint 1] will get [template] metadata from a redis key stored on redis with following structure "template:en:{product_id}:json"
    * Redis key "template:en:(product_id):json" will contain [template] metadata composed by a FabricJS in JSON format and template dimentions following [template_metadata_example] structure.
    * Using [template] metadata, iterate on every text object and assign a unique {objectId}, despite {objectId} is added to metadata, fabricJS JSON must still be valid.
    * Store modified [template] metadata on a redis key named "template:en:{session_id}:demo:json", key must expire on 60 minutes. {session_id} will be a new 10 characters alphanumeric value.
    * finally, return {session_id} as endpoint response in JSON format.

[Endpoint 2] requirements:
    * Create an endpoint that receives {session_id} and text as request parameters.
    * Recovers metadata based on {session_id}, replace text on corresponding {objectId}
    * Based on [template] metadata and dimentions, generates an image with updated text for endpoint response.
    * Add a preview watermark for result image.
    * Image must be resized from original image dimentions to a 600px width.

